        "category": [
          {
            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} reports several weeks of progressive weakness and says she still has some appetite but cannot eat much at one sitting [MEDDIALOG:C18.9:2]. She also recalls episodes of spontaneous bruising on the insides and backs of her thighs in the past, a symptom that prompted medical evaluation because spontaneous bruises can indicate thrombocytopenia or a coagulation problem [MEDDIALOG:C18.9:1]. She has no documented prior cancer treatment in the record available for this scenario.\n\nHer family history is notable for several relatives who died from cancer, including her mother, half-sister, and paternal grandfather; the reported cancers included melanoma and colon cancer [MEDDIALOG:C18.9:1]. This background has contributed to her concern about malignant disease and her willingness to undergo diagnostic testing.\n\nLifestyle-wise, {patientName} is retired and previously independent in activities of daily living, but her recent weakness has limited her exercise tolerance and social activity [MEDDIALOG:C18.9:2]. No smoking or alcohol misuse is documented in the available evidence, so these are not emphasized in this case."
          }
        ]
      }
